1
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:02,600
Grandma.

2
00:00:02,720 --> 00:00:03,720
Termite mushrooms.

3
00:00:04,080 --> 00:00:05,080
Azaleas.

4
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:07,100
Come in, come in.

5
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:07,919
Hurry, hurry!

6
00:00:07,919 --> 00:00:08,679
Change your shoes.

7
00:00:08,720 --> 00:00:10,759
Oh, this is wonderful.

8
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:12,679
- Grandma.
- Changyang is here!

9
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:13,519
Hello, Auntie.

10
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:14,678
Come on in, hurry.

11
00:00:14,679 --> 00:00:14,880
Okay.

12
00:00:14,881 --> 00:00:16,201
I have food cooking on the stove.

13
00:00:16,280 --> 00:00:17,280
Come on in.

14
00:00:17,719 --> 00:00:21,600
Junjun, count for Grandma.

15
00:00:21,719 --> 00:00:23,280
How many times has Grandma invited you?

16
00:00:23,879 --> 00:00:24,879
According to WeChat,

17
00:00:24,879 --> 00:00:25,879
no less than ten times.

18
00:00:26,399 --> 00:00:27,559
Twelve times.

19
00:00:27,679 --> 00:00:28,079
Ah.

20
00:00:28,080 --> 00:00:30,959
Well, whenever I see
those mushrooms,

21
00:00:30,960 --> 00:00:31,600
Grandma,

22
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:32,280
I think of you.

23
00:00:32,280 --> 00:00:33,000
Hey, Grandma.

24
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:34,280
I'm back too.

25
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Grandma.

26
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:37,200
Grandma.

27
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:39,720
I was so worried my cooking
wouldn't taste as good as yours.

28
00:00:40,079 --> 00:00:42,600
Qingtian gains ten pounds every
time he comes back from Molie.

29
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:46,280
He always comes home raving
about how well Changyang cooks.

30
00:00:46,799 --> 00:00:48,200
Kids his age...

31
00:00:49,079 --> 00:00:50,479
can't do anything on their own.

32
00:00:52,079 --> 00:00:54,280
He feels so inadequate around you.

33
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:56,400
It's not that big of a deal.

34
00:00:56,520 --> 00:00:58,479
I've just spent a lot of
time in the mountains.

35
00:00:58,520 --> 00:00:59,520
If you keep doing the same thing,

36
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:00,520
anyone can do it well.

37
00:01:00,521 --> 00:01:02,280
My eldest grandson, come here, quick!

38
00:01:03,679 --> 00:01:04,879
Look, look.

39
00:01:05,319 --> 00:01:06,680
Is it Christmas today?

40
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:11,280
These are all gifts from Junjun.

41
00:01:11,519 --> 00:01:13,000
And this outfit too.

42
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:15,680
Look, does it look good?

43
00:01:18,359 --> 00:01:19,079
Does it look good?

44
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:20,079
It looks great, Grandma.

45
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:31,300
"A Winter Sun Wakes the Wind in Spring Hills' Dream"

46
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:38,500
(Episode 8: Hunter)

47
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,718
Sing, sing!

48
00:01:39,719 --> 00:01:41,159
I'm so hungry, so hungry, so hungry.

49
00:01:41,319 --> 00:01:42,120
I'm really so hungry.

50
00:01:42,121 --> 00:01:43,919
You should sing too!

51
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:45,879
If you don't know how, just learn.

52
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:46,879
You teach me.

53
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,040
Learn it yourself.

54
00:01:48,041 --> 00:01:49,519
Let's eat first. After dinner,

55
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:51,079
you can teach him.

56
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:52,920
Sure. He's tone-deaf, though.

57
00:01:53,159 --> 00:01:54,199
I actually sing very well.

58
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:57,039
Since it's my first time here today,

59
00:01:57,040 --> 00:01:58,239
I'll show off a bit.

60
00:01:58,359 --> 00:02:00,480
Next time I come, I won't cook.

61
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:02,159
I'll leave it all to Changyang.

62
00:02:02,239 --> 00:02:03,239
Sure.

63
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:05,479
Did you hear that? You're cooking.

64
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:05,879
Okay.

65
00:02:05,879 --> 00:02:06,879
Haha.

66
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:08,520
Why do I feel like the outsider here?

67
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,080
You're a regular guest here.

68
00:02:12,719 --> 00:02:13,999
He made preparations in advance.

69
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:17,680
Eat up! Why isn't anyone eating? Come on.

70
00:02:19,719 --> 00:02:20,719
Grandma,

71
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:22,159
when did you find out?

72
00:02:22,719 --> 00:02:23,879
Two years ago.

73
00:02:24,919 --> 00:02:27,639
Junjun told me when he added me on WeChat.

74
00:02:27,879 --> 00:02:29,439
He said he was a fan of yours.

75
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:30,919
And he also said...

76
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,119
he liked you...

77
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:33,639
and wanted to date you.

78
00:02:34,159 --> 00:02:36,240
Grandma, I never said that.

79
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:39,959
Alright, Grandma will stop talking.

80
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:40,639
Let's eat, let's eat.

81
00:02:40,639 --> 00:02:41,639
Eat up.

82
00:02:43,039 --> 00:02:43,719
Get some food for Grandma.

83
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:45,280
Sure thing.

84
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:51,120
My brother took Changyang home.

85
00:02:54,439 --> 00:02:56,239
Mr. Xu, this contract has been approved.

86
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,600
There's also an overseas contract.

87
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,200
I'll work on it as soon as I get back.

88
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,240
Go ahead.

89
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,240
Okay.

90
00:03:11,439 --> 00:03:12,478
Changyang is like a hunter,

91
00:03:12,479 --> 00:03:13,520
and you're like a trap.

92
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:16,680
How so?

93
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:19,240
One chases after the prey,

94
00:03:19,439 --> 00:03:21,280
while the other waits
for the prey to fall in.

95
00:03:21,879 --> 00:03:23,560
That doesn't seem quite right.

96
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,879
I've been the one chasing your brother.

97
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:28,895
Changyang was the one hiding
in the mountains setting traps.

98
00:03:28,919 --> 00:03:29,879
Thinking back now,

99
00:03:29,879 --> 00:03:30,879
it doesn't seem that way.

100
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:33,359
Changyang has been chasing
in the woods for two years.

101
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:35,719
He has both my mom's
and my grandma's WeChat.

102
00:03:35,879 --> 00:03:37,919
He sends tea and mushrooms
to my family every year.

103
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:39,359
He even bought colorful dresses

104
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,680
for my grandma in Tianyi.

105
00:03:40,719 --> 00:03:42,478
You threw tens of
millions of dollars out there,

106
00:03:42,479 --> 00:03:45,135
but it didn't make as much of an
impact as Changyang's few thousand.

107
00:03:45,159 --> 00:03:46,560
I admit defeat completely.

108
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:50,280
Brother Wenshu, are you giving up?

109
00:03:50,879 --> 00:03:54,159
No. I want to be the
eternal white moonlight.

110
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:07,080
Deep in Molie, there's a camellia Village.

111
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,479
I wanted to take you there,

112
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:12,639
but maybe next year. This year,
I could only bring it back to you.

113
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,120
Come in.

114
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:17,759
Are you trying to make me
remember you even after I die?

115
00:05:18,759 --> 00:05:20,799
I want to be remembered
by you even after I'm gone.

116
00:05:24,439 --> 00:05:25,439
I'm an actor.

117
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,000
I'm very emotional.

118
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:33,040
Doing this makes it very easy
for me to get into character.

119
00:05:34,639 --> 00:05:35,639
I won't stop you.

120
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:39,079
The ultimate hunter.

121
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:46,079
You should seriously
consider Director Li's project.

122
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,480
I really like her style,

123
00:06:49,759 --> 00:06:51,879
but I'm really not in the
mood to act right now.

124
00:06:52,279 --> 00:06:53,439
A secret relationship.

125
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:55,480
There's no other way.

126
00:06:56,279 --> 00:06:57,439
The contract is finalized.

127
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:06,079
I heard Kevin's side signed
a new drama with Qi Haoyu.

128
00:07:06,439 --> 00:07:08,479
He's confirmed as the second
male lead in an idol drama,

129
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:09,735
and they're fighting for the male lead.

130
00:07:09,759 --> 00:07:11,318
It's a romantic pairing,

131
00:07:11,319 --> 00:07:12,360
and there are kiss scenes.

132
00:07:13,839 --> 00:07:15,120
Kevin is actually quite honest.

133
00:07:15,839 --> 00:07:17,240
I asked around.

134
00:07:17,319 --> 00:07:18,920
Kevin's side didn't say anything.

135
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,079
Exactly the same.

136
00:07:27,639 --> 00:07:29,479
Let's write his character
off in the spin-off.

137
00:07:30,439 --> 00:07:32,639
If he's more clear-headed than Shi Yuhao,

138
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,839
he might still be saved.

139
00:07:34,959 --> 00:07:36,079
There's one more thing.

140
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:39,040
Sister Lan had booked an MV shoot before.

141
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:42,039
Brother Guo only found out
when checking Lang Di's schedule.

142
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:43,760
The shooting contract is already finalized.

143
00:07:43,959 --> 00:07:45,560
It was originally scheduled for July.

144
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:48,040
Didn't the brand push for it?

145
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:50,696
Maybe the brand has a good
relationship with Sister Lan,

146
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:53,320
or maybe they wanted to lie low
during the controversy back then.

147
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:58,560
Sure.

148
00:07:59,079 --> 00:08:00,240
I'll choose the location.

149
00:08:01,079 --> 00:08:02,719
The location needs to
be chosen by the brand.

150
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:05,079
The place you choose might
not fit the brand's image.

151
00:08:05,879 --> 00:08:07,240
Let the director figure it out.

152
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:08,880
There can't be a male and female lead.

153
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,120
I'll do it myself.

154
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,600
We can have Director Li direct it.

155
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:14,438
It's a good opportunity before the movie

156
00:08:14,439 --> 00:08:15,519
for us to collaborate

157
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,560
and build some hype.

158
00:08:20,759 --> 00:08:21,759
It's impossible to shoot.

159
00:08:22,879 --> 00:08:23,879
Sister,

160
00:08:29,530 --> 00:08:34,630
(Qi Haoyu, we debuted together, [starting]
from nobodies to where we are now,

161
00:08:35,089 --> 00:08:40,023
we have popularity and commercial
endorsements as a result of our work together.

162
00:08:40,250 --> 00:08:45,256
Without this partnership, we might've still been bit actors with no commercial value.]

163
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:48,576
No matter what the commercial
motives were behind our activities,

164
00:08:48,969 --> 00:08:51,289
the hearts of our fans deserve the greatest respect.

165
00:08:51,823 --> 00:08:56,309
Their love for us is genuine, and
their efforts should be rewarded.

166
00:08:57,043 --> 00:09:02,336
I despise how you use your volatile
emotions as a way to hide from reality.

167
00:09:02,923 --> 00:09:06,483
The most shameful act is benefitting
from betraying someone's trust.]

168
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:09,400
these words sound a lot like
what I said to Shi Yuhao back then.

169
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:12,759
How did you handle it later?

170
00:09:13,159 --> 00:09:14,159
Our relationship?

171
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:16,120
Yeah.

172
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,559
Do you love Qi Haoyu?

173
00:09:22,620 --> 00:09:23,700
I do like him.

174
00:09:24,279 --> 00:09:26,879
Even though he can be
a bit crazy sometimes.

175
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:31,039
Falling in love through
acting is easy. But is it love?

176
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,159
What exactly is love?

177
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,320
Put it this way.

178
00:09:39,519 --> 00:09:41,559
I used to think I loved Shi Yuhao,

179
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:44,240
because he could always affect my emotions.

180
00:09:46,879 --> 00:09:49,278
Whether he annoyed me

181
00:09:49,279 --> 00:09:50,440
or ignored me,

182
00:09:50,639 --> 00:09:52,080
I would cry my eyes out.

183
00:09:52,639 --> 00:09:54,679
I told Sister Lan everything back then.

184
00:09:55,039 --> 00:09:56,480
She taught me a skill.

185
00:09:57,320 --> 00:10:00,639
She told me to step back when emotions hit,

186
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:02,480
observe my own feelings,

187
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:05,919
look inward, and talk to myself.

188
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:10,120
Ask myself why I'm crying,

189
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:12,879
and why I'm feeling sad or hurt.

190
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:17,039
Later, I found this method very useful.

191
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:20,279
It really helps heal my
uncontrollable emotions.

192
00:10:21,519 --> 00:10:24,919
Sister Lan said many people make
spiritual practice sound mysterious,

193
00:10:26,279 --> 00:10:29,638
but what everyone
actually needs to practice

194
00:10:29,639 --> 00:10:31,480
is how to regulate their emotions.

195
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:34,320
Only when you can control your emotions

196
00:10:34,639 --> 00:10:35,879
can you control your destiny.

197
00:10:38,039 --> 00:10:39,919
I cried because of Shi Yuhao

198
00:10:40,679 --> 00:10:43,080
because I was always
focused on how he treated me.

199
00:10:47,039 --> 00:10:48,639
But when I looked closely at myself,

200
00:10:49,215 --> 00:10:51,735
I realized I didn't like
him as much as I thought.

201
00:10:52,213 --> 00:10:54,535
I only liked the character in the drama.

202
00:10:54,655 --> 00:10:56,056
Looking at it another way,

203
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,480
it wasn't Shi Yuhao's fault either.

204
00:10:57,879 --> 00:10:59,359
We just had an emotional accident

205
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:01,519
at an age when we didn't understand love.

206
00:11:02,039 --> 00:11:03,240
Now I understand.

207
00:11:03,919 --> 00:11:06,159
Love is keeping someone in your instincts,

208
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:09,440
always caring about whether they need you.

209
00:11:15,279 --> 00:11:16,320
I didn't come to see you.

210
00:11:23,159 --> 00:11:24,479
President Fang asked me to be the guide.

211
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:27,279
She said you're going to Molie
to shoot an MV. Are you crazy?

212
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:30,519
Crazy? Like a bear shot with an arrow,

213
00:11:30,679 --> 00:11:31,960
running wild in the woods.

214
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,440
Where did it get shot?

215
00:11:47,159 --> 00:11:48,279
Hey, Brother Peng.

216
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:51,080
I'm heading into the mountains
with Lang Di to shoot an MV.

217
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:55,120
Will you pass by Xi Gui?

218
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:57,456
I was worried you'd get carsick,

219
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:58,640
so we didn't take that route.

220
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,440
We'll stop by on our way back.

221
00:12:01,919 --> 00:12:02,919
Okay.

222
00:12:03,919 --> 00:12:05,720
Oh, the timing doesn't work out.

223
00:12:06,279 --> 00:12:09,240
How about this? Give Jialin a call.

224
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:10,879
Hey? Hello?

225
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:16,240
Why aren't Brother Guo
and Yezi staying here?

226
00:13:17,759 --> 00:13:19,639
To keep you from
disturbing the peace at night.

227
00:13:32,879 --> 00:13:33,879
Come up.

228
00:13:34,159 --> 00:13:35,159
Come down.

229
00:13:35,879 --> 00:13:36,879
Come up.

230
00:13:36,919 --> 00:13:37,919
Come down.

231
00:13:50,039 --> 00:13:51,119
Disturbing the peace, huh?

232
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,416
Let's see how I disturb the peace tonight.

233
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:53,880
Show me how you're going to do that.

234
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:01,080
Bro, can you do another livestream for me?

235
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:04,840
Selling what?

236
00:14:06,879 --> 00:14:09,080
These are all hand-embroidered
by the local weavers.

237
00:14:15,759 --> 00:14:16,759
Charity again?

238
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:18,639
Of course, that's why I came to you.

239
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:23,440
Alright. Go ask Brother Guo to schedule it.

240
00:14:23,519 --> 00:14:25,038
Thanks, Bro! You're the best.

241
00:14:25,039 --> 00:14:26,440
Oh, cut it out.

242
00:14:36,879 --> 00:14:38,240
So if we hadn't come,

243
00:14:38,279 --> 00:14:40,159
you weren't planning on
returning to Shangjing?

244
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:41,960
We've traveled to so many places.

245
00:14:43,279 --> 00:14:44,719
Tian drives all day long.

246
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:46,000
A month just flies by like that.

247
00:14:46,879 --> 00:14:48,279
It's been almost two months, right?

248
00:14:48,752 --> 00:14:51,113
Qingtian took me to six coffee estates.

249
00:14:51,326 --> 00:14:52,846
And four tea estates.

250
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:59,240
It works out perfectly since I
applied for an off-campus internship.

251
00:14:59,559 --> 00:15:02,120
Changyang, can you ask
your cousin to stamp my form?

252
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:03,679
Sure, I have the stamp with me.

253
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,720
How convenient.

254
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:19,678
Should I, as your guardian,

255
00:15:19,679 --> 00:15:21,639
write a little note for you?

256
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:24,240
Appears to be an internship,

257
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:26,279
but actually a vacation.

258
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:29,440
False advertising.

259
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,240
Who's false advertising?

260
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,440
Appears to be a shoot,

261
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:36,559
but actually a honeymoon.

262
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:39,480
Feng Qingtian!

263
00:15:39,519 --> 00:15:40,519
Feng Qinglang!

264
00:15:50,033 --> 00:15:51,273
Your cousin's company?

265
00:15:51,505 --> 00:15:52,705
Changyang is a shareholder.

266
00:16:02,159 --> 00:16:04,559
It was your company that
asked me to shoot the MV.

267
00:16:05,159 --> 00:16:05,960
At the end of last year,

268
00:16:05,961 --> 00:16:07,481
I booked the schedule with Sister Lan.

269
00:16:08,919 --> 00:16:11,279
So even if I didn't go
into the mountains in April,

270
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:13,559
I couldn't escape it in July.

271
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,600
You were destined to be caught.

272
00:16:20,279 --> 00:16:23,080
Can you two stop being
so affectionate here?

273
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:36,080
Come down.

274
00:16:43,213 --> 00:16:46,093
My brother can be quite stubborn.

275
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:50,639
You're much better.

276
00:17:01,766 --> 00:17:05,253
You've prepared so much,
what if I wasn't interested in you?

277
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:08,159
Is that possible?

278
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:42,319
Aren't you two heading back with us?

279
00:17:44,359 --> 00:17:47,279
Who knows how many more days you
two will be lovey-dovey after the shoot.

280
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:51,920
Brother Wenshu doesn't seem very happy.

281
00:17:52,319 --> 00:17:54,519
Can you tone it down a bit in front of him?

282
00:17:54,960 --> 00:17:57,319
At least don't get between the Xu brothers.

283
00:17:57,559 --> 00:17:58,839
Was I that bad?

284
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:01,120
You were totally over the top.

285
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,000
I've said my piece. I'm off.

286
00:18:03,519 --> 00:18:04,559
Back to Shangjing?

287
00:18:05,119 --> 00:18:07,239
Brother Wenshu is driving
me back to the Tea College.

288
00:18:09,799 --> 00:18:10,799
Let's go.

289
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:23,319
Yezi, give me your phone.

290
00:18:26,580 --> 00:18:30,080
[The last message from God of
Wealth Xu: Interesting, see you later.]

291
00:18:31,426 --> 00:18:33,593
[Take good care of my younger brother!]

292
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:55,720
Tian,

293
00:18:56,759 --> 00:18:58,759
can you give me a ride to
town to buy some things?

294
00:18:58,960 --> 00:18:59,960
Hop in.

295
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:06,440
How long does it take to get to town?

296
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:07,720
About half an hour.

297
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:08,960
Oh, okay.

298
00:19:08,961 --> 00:19:10,401
That won't delay my hair and makeup.

299
00:19:24,426 --> 00:19:25,505
I made it.

300
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:27,160
How are you getting back?

301
00:19:27,359 --> 00:19:28,319
The lighting truck will be here soon.

302
00:19:28,320 --> 00:19:29,559
I'll hitch a ride back then.

303
00:19:29,759 --> 00:19:31,640
Alright, we'll head out first.

304
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:32,720
Thanks, Mr. Xu.

305
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,240
Fell asleep.

306
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,000
Okay, cut!

307
00:20:57,039 --> 00:20:58,039
Let's watch the playback.

308
00:21:08,319 --> 00:21:09,960
Your company's planning is pretty good.

309
00:21:11,160 --> 00:21:12,719
I invited Director Li to shoot this.

310
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:13,799
It's within budget.

311
00:21:13,839 --> 00:21:15,000
I pulled some favors.

312
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:18,440
Your face is indeed quite valuable.

313
00:21:19,799 --> 00:21:21,719
Director Li wants me to
star in her new project.

314
00:21:22,039 --> 00:21:23,039
Take it!

315
00:21:26,559 --> 00:21:27,639
I'm not in the mood to act.

316
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:33,559
You don't even want to pretend anymore.

317
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:46,599
Changyang,

318
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:48,160
look at this angle.

319
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:49,640
Coming!

320
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:09,399
Oh, stop fooling around, you two.

321
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:10,960
We're about to shoot. Go back.

322
00:22:17,839 --> 00:22:18,839
I'm off.

323
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:42,839
Let me take a picture of you, Guo.

324
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:44,519
This hat really suits you.

325
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:45,319
Really?

326
00:22:45,319 --> 00:22:46,319
Yes, come on.

327
00:22:47,559 --> 00:22:48,919
Oh my.

328
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:49,920
So beautiful.

329
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:52,200
You've still got it!

330
00:22:52,319 --> 00:22:53,558
What do you mean, 'still got it'?

331
00:22:53,559 --> 00:22:55,159
A friend of mine wants to shoot

332
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,839
a documentary about the tea mountains.

333
00:22:57,039 --> 00:22:58,200
They need a male lead.

334
00:22:59,319 --> 00:23:00,559
He's really not cut out for it.

335
00:23:00,839 --> 00:23:02,519
Documentaries don't require acting skills.

336
00:23:02,599 --> 00:23:03,639
He wouldn't want to do it.

337
00:23:04,160 --> 00:23:05,318
You can cast my brother.

338
00:23:05,319 --> 00:23:07,519
My brother is even more handsome than me.

339
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:09,318
Plus, he comes to Molie every year,

340
00:23:09,319 --> 00:23:10,399
so he knows the place well.

341
00:23:10,799 --> 00:23:12,000
Then introduce us.

342
00:23:16,359 --> 00:23:17,640
Do I look beautiful?

343
00:23:21,039 --> 00:23:22,159
Send it to me later.

344
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:23,160
Okay.

345
00:23:26,119 --> 00:23:27,359
Director Li has her eye on you.

346
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:28,720
For what?

347
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:31,240
What else when a director
has her eye on you?

348
00:23:31,519 --> 00:23:32,519
Lang Di,

349
00:23:32,799 --> 00:23:33,799
coming!

350
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,319
This one is even prettier.

351
00:24:06,359 --> 00:24:08,279
Not everyone on the crew is one of us.

352
00:24:33,359 --> 00:24:34,359
199.

353
00:25:09,960 --> 00:25:11,160
Got in this afternoon.

354
00:25:15,799 --> 00:25:16,559
Dad.

355
00:25:16,559 --> 00:25:17,559
Yeah.

356
00:25:26,578 --> 00:25:28,378
Changyang's roasted tea
is good for the stomach.

357
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:29,640
Oh?

358
00:25:42,599 --> 00:25:44,679
Mainly because I don't
know how to brew it properly.

359
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:46,359
Steeping it directly is simpler.

360
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:48,160
Have a seat.

361
00:25:54,079 --> 00:25:55,079
Good tea.

362
00:25:57,500 --> 00:25:59,300
How is your mother doing in the UK?

363
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:03,559
She's fine, though she's
still not used to the weather.

364
00:26:13,045 --> 00:26:14,646
Thinking of coming back to work here?

365
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:17,200
No.

366
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:19,680
I only came back because of an opportunity.

367
00:26:19,799 --> 00:26:20,799
What opportunity?

368
00:26:23,279 --> 00:26:24,480
An old friend passed away.

369
00:26:27,359 --> 00:26:30,680
The producer of the film you invested in?

370
00:26:31,799 --> 00:26:32,799
Yes.

371
00:26:34,359 --> 00:26:36,799
Don't get too close to people in showbiz.

372
00:26:37,680 --> 00:26:41,599
A single photo can
easily be misinterpreted.

373
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:43,480
I understand.

374
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:55,680
Your aunt recently introduced a girl to me.

375
00:26:56,240 --> 00:26:57,599
She's great in every aspect,

376
00:26:58,480 --> 00:27:00,160
and she also studied abroad.

377
00:27:04,799 --> 00:27:06,160
Since you're back,

378
00:27:07,119 --> 00:27:08,279
go meet her.

379
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:37,480
President Fang,

380
00:27:37,680 --> 00:27:40,160
Kevin's side refused to shoot for
the magazine we recommended.

381
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:42,358
Seeing Qi Haoyu taking their side,

382
00:27:42,359 --> 00:27:43,559
they've started playing hardball.

383
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:57,680
Qi Haoyu,

384
00:27:58,640 --> 00:27:59,440
Han Lu told me

385
00:27:59,441 --> 00:28:01,400
you haven't been replying to his messages.

386
00:28:01,839 --> 00:28:03,880
This is also the last time I'll call you.

387
00:28:04,359 --> 00:28:06,359
You debuted as a duo with Han Lu

388
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:07,960
to get the traffic you have today.

389
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:10,799
Your appearance fee for a single
commercial event is now 100,000.

390
00:28:11,559 --> 00:28:13,279
If you're willing to keep cooperating,

391
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:14,480
there's no limit.

392
00:28:14,759 --> 00:28:16,599
Don't tell me you don't care about money.

393
00:28:16,799 --> 00:28:18,599
Look at your classmates.

394
00:28:18,680 --> 00:28:21,176
After graduation, they're still doing
short dramas for 800 yuan for four days.

395
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:23,440
And there's a crowd
fighting to perform for free.

396
00:28:23,759 --> 00:28:25,838
If you want to go back to
acting in those trashy web dramas,

397
00:28:25,839 --> 00:28:26,839
no one is stopping you.

398
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:29,799
Our company has never cast
artists from other agencies.

399
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:32,160
You were an exception
specially approved by Sister Lan.

400
00:28:32,799 --> 00:28:35,839
If you're cutting ties just
because Sister Lan is gone,

401
00:28:36,200 --> 00:28:38,399
then we all misjudged you.

402
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:40,960
Many follow-up tasks
are bound by the contract.

403
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,839
Now, because of your attitude,

404
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:44,679
your agency is refusing to cooperate.

405
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:46,680
We don't want to take this to court.

406
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:49,278
Jialan Shanying would
rather discard you as a pawn

407
00:28:49,279 --> 00:28:51,640
than drag this fight in front of the fans.

408
00:28:51,799 --> 00:28:53,359
Think about it carefully.

409
00:28:53,480 --> 00:28:55,799
Kevin didn't agree to the
magazine we arranged.

410
00:28:56,072 --> 00:28:57,953
If you shoot Kevin's choice,

411
00:28:58,359 --> 00:29:00,359
I'll have Han Lu cooperate with you,

412
00:29:00,559 --> 00:29:02,319
but we won't have a
future together anymore.

413
00:29:16,599 --> 00:29:17,599
Where is everyone?

414
00:29:20,440 --> 00:29:21,359
Want some water?

415
00:29:21,359 --> 00:29:22,359
Over here.

416
00:29:24,599 --> 00:29:27,839
Come on, makeup, wardrobe,
photographer, camera assistant.

417
00:29:32,440 --> 00:29:35,359
Hello, everyone.

418
00:29:37,039 --> 00:29:37,880
Lao Xie.

419
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:39,038
This is Mr. Qi.

420
00:29:39,039 --> 00:29:40,200
This is Mr. Han.

421
00:29:41,759 --> 00:29:42,599
Hello, Mr. Hu.

422
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:43,640
Hello, Mr. Chen.

423
00:29:46,200 --> 00:29:49,200
You got it wrong. This
is Mr. Qi and Mr. Han.

424
00:29:50,960 --> 00:29:52,599
Mr. Nie, Mr. Liu.

425
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:55,255
There are too many CP ships
lately. I'm getting them all mixed up.

426
00:29:55,279 --> 00:29:57,200
It's fine. Come on.

427
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:04,599
Come touch up their makeup.

428
00:30:21,559 --> 00:30:22,960
Hey, where did you two go?

429
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,959
I managed to get the company to agree

430
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:30,560
to a joint magazine shoot with you guys.

431
00:30:32,799 --> 00:30:33,799
That's great.

432
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:36,400
Don't you want to know how I got it?

433
00:30:37,440 --> 00:30:38,440
Not interested.

434
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:42,720
Are you not interested
in me anymore either?

435
00:30:45,160 --> 00:30:46,240
Was I ever?

436
00:31:00,960 --> 00:31:01,960
Hurry up and shoot.

437
00:31:02,599 --> 00:31:03,599
Let me.

438
00:31:04,400 --> 00:31:05,039
Oh my.

439
00:31:05,040 --> 00:31:07,480
Editor-in-chief, this won't
sell. It's useless to shoot this.

440
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:09,495
The two of them are
really good at selling it.

441
00:31:09,519 --> 00:31:11,200
I meant the magazine.

442
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:12,720
The overseas edition will sell.

443
00:31:13,079 --> 00:31:14,680
Lao Xie, take more photos.

444
00:31:22,366 --> 00:31:31,679
[Fans freaking out over the magazine
shoot [which is somehow already out?]]

445
00:31:31,739 --> 00:31:34,652
[Some negative comments about how BL stars are
only in it for the money, or the shoot being bad]

446
00:31:34,676 --> 00:31:37,527
[Xu Wenzhu: Hello, sorry, I
won't make our meeting.

447
00:31:37,551 --> 00:31:42,016
First let me apologize, and
then say that I don't like women.]

448
00:31:42,599 --> 00:31:45,079
Do you know who the girl you met is?

449
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:49,279
Is your sexual orientation something
you can just talk about so casually?

450
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:55,200
You've known about my
orientation for a long time,

451
00:31:55,559 --> 00:31:57,559
yet you still set me up
on blind dates with girls.

452
00:31:58,599 --> 00:32:01,239
Did you show any respect to either of us?

453
00:32:01,240 --> 00:32:02,480
Don't talk to me about respect.

454
00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:05,279
Only normal people deserve my respect.

455
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:10,960
So,

456
00:32:11,599 --> 00:32:13,480
is finding two women considered normal?

457
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:15,200
Or,

458
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:17,799
is finding even more
women even more normal?

459
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:34,200
Hello?

460
00:32:34,599 --> 00:32:36,400
Hello, Brother Wenshu.

461
00:32:36,799 --> 00:32:38,599
Are you in Shangjing?

462
00:32:38,759 --> 00:32:40,799
What's wrong? Don't panic, take your time.

463
00:32:42,359 --> 00:32:45,799
The caregiver messaged me saying
Brother Chen Zhu is in critical condition.

464
00:32:46,200 --> 00:32:47,798
I bought a ticket to fly back.

465
00:32:47,799 --> 00:32:49,798
Can you pick me up from the airport?

466
00:32:49,799 --> 00:32:50,799
What time do you arrive?

467
00:32:52,240 --> 00:32:53,240
9:30.

468
00:32:53,759 --> 00:32:55,839
Okay, I'll wait for you at the airport.

469
00:33:02,799 --> 00:33:03,799
The flight is delayed.

470
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:06,240
I don't know when I can leave.

471
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:08,759
I've been in touch with the caregiver.

472
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:10,775
He's keeping me updated
on Chen Zhu's condition.

473
00:33:10,799 --> 00:33:11,799
He's stable for now.

474
00:33:12,039 --> 00:33:13,680
Just wait for your flight calmly.

475
00:33:13,960 --> 00:33:15,279
Let me know when you board.

476
00:33:16,200 --> 00:33:18,359
I'm afraid I won't get
to see him one last time.

477
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:35,279
You're Qingtian.

478
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:39,559
Auntie, how is Brother Chen Zhu doing now?

479
00:33:39,799 --> 00:33:41,359
Don't you dare say my son's name!

480
00:33:41,559 --> 00:33:42,559
Get out!

481
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:43,799
This is all your fault!

482
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:46,160
You caused my son's car accident! Get out!

483
00:33:46,759 --> 00:33:48,359
Get out! Get out!

484
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:55,960
Uncle, Auntie,

485
00:33:56,279 --> 00:33:57,960
I'm Chen Zhu's high school classmate,

486
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:59,039
class monitor Wenshu.

487
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:02,799
I'm here to visit him on
behalf of our Class 2 alumni.

488
00:34:03,559 --> 00:34:04,640
We don't need this.

489
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:06,038
Do you think if you all come,

490
00:34:06,039 --> 00:34:07,759
my son will wake up?

491
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:08,840
Will he wake up?

492
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:10,759
It's you. It's all your fault.

493
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:11,840
It's all your fault!

494
00:34:12,159 --> 00:34:13,800
Why did you have to ruin him?

495
00:34:14,280 --> 00:34:15,679
Why my son?

496
00:34:16,360 --> 00:34:19,400
Why did it have to be my son?

497
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:22,159
There are so many boys in Class 2,

498
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:24,200
and even the class monitor is here.

499
00:34:24,239 --> 00:34:26,159
Why did you have to be gay with him?

500
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:28,158
Why my son?

501
00:34:28,159 --> 00:34:29,159
You're gay!

502
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:30,600
Why did you have to go after him?

503
00:34:33,480 --> 00:34:37,039
My son, why did it
have to be you? My son...

504
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:39,960
Fasten your seatbelt.

505
00:35:50,019 --> 00:35:55,179
[Messages sent from the caregiver to both of them
saying Chen Zhu is out of danger and not to rush]

506
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:03,000
I'm not going anymore.

507
00:36:04,400 --> 00:36:05,760
As long as I'm still your father,

508
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:07,960
I will never let you be with a man.

509
00:36:09,599 --> 00:36:11,159
Damn it, do you even know how to drive?

510
00:36:13,360 --> 00:36:14,360
You...

511
00:36:29,519 --> 00:36:31,559
Is our son sick?

512
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:18,760
He got into the car
accident while calling me.

513
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:29,920
He got into the car
accident while calling me.

514
00:37:32,480 --> 00:37:34,920
He got into the car
accident while calling me.

515
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:51,800
It's so hot.

516
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:58,000
It smells bad. My hand is burnt.

517
00:38:10,119 --> 00:38:11,800
Keep yesterday's tea cake for me.

518
00:38:14,119 --> 00:38:15,159
Keep it until when?

519
00:38:31,760 --> 00:38:32,760
Keep it until when?

520
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:39,159
Keep it until we can stand
proudly in front of everyone.

521
00:38:40,199 --> 00:38:43,159
Okay, I'll have my cousin put it in
the temperature-controlled tea cellar.

522
00:38:50,119 --> 00:38:51,400
Xu Jinbai wants to see you.

523
00:38:52,519 --> 00:38:53,519
Your dad?

524
00:38:57,360 --> 00:38:58,920
I came out to my mom.

525
00:38:59,519 --> 00:39:00,719
She'll definitely tell Old Xu.

526
00:39:02,320 --> 00:39:03,960
But I didn't expect it to be this soon.

527
00:39:11,320 --> 00:39:12,679
What do you want me to do?

528
00:39:18,679 --> 00:39:19,760
Just be yourself.

529
00:39:37,719 --> 00:39:39,639
Why didn't you bring
the director here to shoot?

530
00:39:40,519 --> 00:39:41,519
It's a secret base.

531
00:39:41,719 --> 00:39:43,159
It can't be shared with anyone else.

532
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:16,280
I don't like winding mountain roads.

533
00:40:17,320 --> 00:40:18,320
They're like tracks.

534
00:40:19,400 --> 00:40:21,360
Too narrow and too crowded.

535
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:25,880
Only at the end of the
tracks is the open wilderness.

536
00:42:20,119 --> 00:42:21,479
We're having dinner at
Changyang's place tomorrow.

537
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:23,080
He said we don't need to bring anything.

538
00:42:24,360 --> 00:42:26,119
Bring a dozen signed photos.

539
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:27,320
Photo cards work too.

540
00:42:27,679 --> 00:42:28,679
Get lost.

541
00:42:33,519 --> 00:42:35,639
He brought so many gifts
when he came over last time.

542
00:42:35,960 --> 00:42:38,280
It wouldn't be right if I
didn't bring anything, would it?

543
00:42:38,519 --> 00:42:40,519
He's someone who's used to giving gifts.

544
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:42,920
As they say, he has high
emotional intelligence.

545
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:44,000
Do you?

546
00:42:45,199 --> 00:42:46,559
Are you calling me socially inept?

547
00:42:47,599 --> 00:42:49,535
Low EQ just means being
straightforward and direct.

548
00:42:49,559 --> 00:42:50,679
It's also a virtue.

549
00:42:56,599 --> 00:42:58,280
Are you afraid his family won't like you?

550
00:43:00,880 --> 00:43:01,880
Not really.

551
00:43:02,679 --> 00:43:03,679
I just can't explain it.

552
00:43:07,360 --> 00:43:09,599
Brother, are you serious?

553
00:43:10,360 --> 00:43:11,360
About what?

554
00:43:11,599 --> 00:43:12,599
About Changyang.

555
00:43:13,079 --> 00:43:14,079
Doesn't it look like it?

556
00:43:15,519 --> 00:43:16,800
Your acting has improved a lot.

557
00:43:18,800 --> 00:43:20,519
I just feel that if I lose him,

558
00:43:20,599 --> 00:43:22,119
there will never be anyone better.

559
00:43:23,599 --> 00:43:24,599
Selfish.

560
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:26,960
All you think about is
your own gains and losses.

561
00:43:28,079 --> 00:43:29,919
Then what was your
relationship with Chen Zhu?

562
00:43:36,119 --> 00:43:37,519
I guess it was love.

563
00:43:40,519 --> 00:43:41,880
If he dies,

564
00:43:42,880 --> 00:43:44,000
I won't go on living either.

565
00:43:50,719 --> 00:43:51,719
Tian.

566
00:43:52,599 --> 00:43:54,879
You wouldn't actually do
something so foolish, would you?

567
00:43:56,679 --> 00:43:58,000
I'm just kidding.

